Sentencas: An Sr0.88Y0.08TiO3-delta (SYT)/La0.4Ce0.6O1.8 (LDC) composite impregnated with Pd was evaluated as a sulfur-tolerant anode for the La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.83Mg0.17O3-delta (LSGM)-supported cells.
Titulo: Pd-impregnated SYT/LDC composite as sulfur-tolerant anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The impregnation of Pd into the porous SYT/LDC anode was found to significantly enhance the anode performance.
Titulo: Pd-impregnated SYT/LDC composite as sulfur-tolerant anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With the addition of 1.5 wt.% Pd into the anode, the anodic overpotential was reduced to about half of the original value.
Titulo: Pd-impregnated SYT/LDC composite as sulfur-tolerant anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The single cell with the Pd-impregnated SYT/LDC anode showed a maximum power density of 1006 and 577 MW cm(-2) at 850 and 800 degrees C in city H-2, respectively, which was more than twice of that prior to impregnation.
Titulo: Pd-impregnated SYT/LDC composite as sulfur-tolerant anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Pd-impregnated composite anode exhibited good tolerance to sulfur, with essentially no decay in performance in H-2 containing up to 50 ppm H2S. (C) 2009
Titulo: Pd-impregnated SYT/LDC composite as sulfur-tolerant anode for solid oxide fuel cells
Pd-impregnated SYT/LDC composite as sulfur-tolerant anode for solid oxide fuel cells
